The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | International | Solace opens in UK to record ticket sales
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Solace opens in UK to record ticket sales
                              Actress Olga Kurylenko at the premiere of Quantum of Solace in Paris. (Reuters)                            
	London, Nov. 1 (Reuters): The new James Bond film, Quantum of Solace, debuted in Britain yesterday to record one-day ticket sales of 4.94 million ($8 million), distributor Columbia Pictures said today.        
	The total tops Harry Potter and the Goblet of Fire, the previous record holder with an opening day haul of 4.025 million ($6.5 million) in 2005, and it also beat the 2.9 million ($4.72 million) first-day total for the last Bond film, Casino Royale (2006), Columbia said.        
	In Quantum of Solace, British super spy Bond (Daniel Craig) is on a mission across South America and Europe to stop an eco-terrorist from controlling precious natural resources, and he wants to learn why the woman he loved in Casino Royale betrayed him.        
	Casino Royale, was a huge box office success with a global haul of $594 million.        
	Yesterdays British opening of Quantum of Solace in 542 theatres will be followed by a November 14 debut of the film in the US and Canada.        
	Columbia Pictures is a division of Sony Pictures Entertainment, the media wing of Japans Sony Corp.        
	Craig was joined at Wednesdays charity gala screening in central London by co-stars including Ukrainian Olga Kurylenko and Bond regular Judi Dench, who had a glittering 007 insignia stuck to the back of her neck.                                                                                                                                                                           
